The paper discusses the use of neural networks for automatic program generation in a DSL language, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the extension of the DSL with new symbols, which relates to programming languages (cs.PL). The use of neural networks for program synthesis is a machine learning technique, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the approach and its application to software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY).
